Slovenia’s Mercator Majority Stake May Be for Sale, Finance Says

-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 
2011-06-15T09:16:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/slovenia-s-mercator-majority-stake-may-be-for-sale-finance-says.html
A group of Slovenian banks and
 Pivovarna Lasko (PILR)  Group d.d., which together own a majority of
 Mercator Poslovni Sistem (MELR)  d.d., agreed to sell their stakes,
Finance said today without saying where it got that information.  The banks include Gorenjska Banka d.d. and Nova Kreditna
Banka Maribor d.d., the business newspaper reported.  Earlier this year, a 23 percent stake in Mercator was
offered by Lasko. Agrokor d.d.,  Croatia ’s largest privately held
company, and private equity groups Mid Europa Partners Ltd. and
Warburg Pincus LLC. on March 10 submitted bids for the stake.
Offers were rejected on May 4.  To contact the reporter on this story: Jasmina Kuzmanovic at
   jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  